n-puzzle
made by XnpioChV

The program recives an image and generates a n-puzzle game (random or your choice). The game can be solve by an algorithm or by the user.

Ussage:

n-puzzle <imageFile>

Options:

-f <matrixFile>: Use a file with a matrix that you want the puzzle starts. If you don't use this option, the start matrix will be generated randomly.
-u: The user solves the puzzle (by default).
-c: The computer solves the puzzle.
-n <number>: The size of the matrix that is n * n (n = 3 by default).

